subject: p19499595
History: Year old woman with hx sternotomy with superficial mid sternal pain to palpation and with deep breaths x 1 month.
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest demonstrate multiple fractured sternal wires, unchanged from. New from, is a posteriorly displaced sternal wire fragment at approximately the mid sternal level. There is no focal consolidation. The cardiomediastinal and hilar contours are stable. There is no pneumothorax or a pleural effusion.
Impression: No interval change to multiple fractured sternal wires. Recommend chest CT to localize a posteriorly displaced wire fragment of the superior third sternal wire.
